http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Enforce-ban-on-smoking-strictly-officials-told/article13987608.ece

Deputy Commissioner M.N. Ajay Nagabhushan on Thursday instructed the police and other departments concerned to deal sternly with those violating the Cigarette and Other Tobacco Products (Prohibition of Advertisement and Regulation of Trade and Commerce, Production, Supply and Distribution) Act (COTPA), 2003.Addressing the officials of various departments here on Thursday, Mr. Nagabhushan urged the officials to undertake special drives across the district at regular intervals under the COTPA and bring those violating its provisions to book. Smoking in public places had been banned. Officials should undertake drives at regular intervals to ensure strict implementation of the ban order, create public awareness about the ban and put on display warning signs at public places, he said.Officials said that they had registered 723 cases against persons charged with violation of the provisions of the Act in the district between June and November 2015, and collected Rs. 86,050 as fine from violators.They also said they had removed 150 hoardings promoting tobacco products from various shops here.